    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-11-10T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-11-10T16:30:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>61. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d61fn0"
                        >Source: Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Trips and Conferences,
                            <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> Trip to Pakistan and
                        Afghanistan, 10/61-11/61. Confidential. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> on November 13. According to the
                        President’s Appointment Book, the meeting was held at the White House.
                        (Ibid.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1961-11-10T16:30:00-05:00"
                            >November 10, 1961, 4:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Conclusions and Recommendations Resulting from my Visit to Pakistan and
                        Afghanistan from Oct. 19 to Nov. 8, 1961, as the Personal Representative of
                        the President of the United States for the Exercise of his Good Offices in
                        Connection with the Stoppage of Transit Traffic to and from Afghanistan
                        through Pakistan</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>The President</item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_TP1">Phillips
                            Talbot</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName>Livingston T. Merchant</persName>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="0162" n="136" xml:id="pg_136"/>
                <p>I reported orally to the President on the results of my mission to Pakistan and
                    Afghanistan along the lines of my reports earlier in the day to Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_TP1">Talbot</persName> and to the Secretary. The views I
                    expressed and the recommendations I made are contained in my memorandum to the
                    Secretary of November 11, 1961.<note n="1" xml:id="d61fn1">Neither this
                        memorandum nor any record of <persName corresp="#p_MLT1"
                        >Merchant</persName>’s meetings with <persName corresp="#p_TP1"
                            >Talbot</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> has
                        been found.</note> The President expressed the keenest interest in the
                    problem and its present status. While the President made no decisions in the
                    matter, I received the impression that he was generally in sympathy with my
                    recommendations. In the matter of the future economic aid program to
                    Afghanistan, he indicated to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_TP1">Talbot</persName>
                    that he would like to have relevant recommendations prepared for his
                    consideration. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_TP1">Talbot</persName> said that these
                    were already under way in consultation with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GWS1"
                        >Gaud</persName> of <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>. At the conclusion
                    of my report, the President thanked me for undertaking the mission.</p>
            </div>
